</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="91" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="91">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="91">
Only the holotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lyonetiidae" genus="Philonome" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Philonome spectata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spectata">Philonome spectata</taxonomicName>
is known to exist. It was not possible to examine this specimen and to illustrate the genitalia. This species can be distinguished from other congeners in lacking the dorsal bar on the forewing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
